  <gettingAround><![CDATA[<h3>Lifts</h3>
<p><span>There are 18 lifts open in Val Gardena during the summer, normally from the beginning of June until early October. I</span>f you're planning to make good use of the lifts in the Val Gardena the <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.valgardena.it/en/summer-holidays-dolomites/mobility/gardena-card/" target="_blank">Gardena Car</a><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.valgardena.it/en/summer-holidays-dolomites/mobility/gardena-card/" target="_blank">d </a>is really useful and may even save you some money or if you want to explore further afield then the <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.dolomitisuperski.com/en/SuperSummer/home" target="_blank">Dolomiti Supersummer</a> pass gives you access to 120 lifts in 15 regions.</p>
<p>For more information on the cards mentioned above check out the 'Cards &amp; Passes' section of this page.</p>
<h3>Public transport</h3>
<p>For Inghams guests the public buses in the Val Gardena are free. All you have to do is take you Val Gardena Mobil Card with you and you'll easily be able to hop from town to town within the area. This opens up even more areas for you to explore!</p>]]></gettingAround>
