  <insidersGuide><![CDATA[<p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Good to know</p>
<p><strong>Walking trails:</strong> 600km of walking trails and easy access to other valleys and mountains in the Dolomites</p>
<p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Varied terrain from mountain climbs to flat, grassy meadows</p>
<p><strong>Best time to go:</strong> June to mid September. It can get hot in August but the high altitude walks are a great way to cool off</p>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> <span>all walking abilities, easy &amp; challenging walks, large walking area, guided walks, high altitude, national parks, wow-factor, food &amp; drink, activities </span></p>
<p><strong>Fly into:</strong> Verona (approx. 2 hours)</p>
<p><strong>Fly from:</strong> Manchester, London Gatwick, Birmingham, Bristol, Edinburgh, Stansted, East Midlands, Leeds Bradford, Newcastle, Belfast</p>
<p><strong>Transfer time:</strong> approx. 3 hours from Verona. Please note transfers could take longer during peak summer months especially when arriving to Verona late afternoon.</p>
<p><strong>Resort Card:</strong> Free Val Gardena Mobil Card</p>
<p><strong>24/7 Support and advice:</strong> In person or over the phone from our local resort team based in Selva</p>
<p><strong>Inghams Guided Walks included</strong></p>]]></insidersGuide>
