  <popularWalkingRoutes><![CDATA[<h3>Rifugio Puez via the Vallunga</h3>
<p>Walk to Rifugio Puez (at 2,475m) via a very picturesque Vallunga Valley. At the end of Vallunga Valley take path 16, which offers stunning views of Sassolungo, the Sella Massif, Sassongher &amp; Sass da Ciampac. Enjoy a nice lunch at Rifugio Puez before heading back down on path 14 where you will be rewarded with stunning panoramic views of the Vallunga Valley.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Moderate-Challenging</li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> approx. 15 kilometres</li>
</ul>
<h3>Monte Pic</h3>
<p>You'll feel on top of the world at the summit of Pic Mountain. Hike up Monte Pic and then head over to Sëurasas. This walk will take you to some of the most scenic viewpoints in Val Gardena. The summit of Mount Pic is well worth a visit for its uninterrupted, 360° views of the Dolomites. From Sëurasas you can walk back down to Ortisei or to the bottom of the Col Raiser Cable Car in Selva.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Moderate-Challenging</li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> approx. 7 kilometres</li>
</ul>
<h3>Round the Sassolungo Group</h3>
<p>Start on the Ciampinoi lift and hike towards the well-known rock formations of the stone city and to the Passo Sella. Follow the Friedrich August path and take in the stunning views over Seiser Alm, the biggest high alpine pasture in Europe.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade: </strong>Moderate-Challenging </li>
<li><strong>Distance: </strong>approx. 17 kilometres</li>
</ul>
<p>You can view more recommended routes with interactive maps on the <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.valgardena.it/en/summer-holidays-dolomites/trekking/hiking-trails/#filter=r-fullyTranslatedLangus-&amp;zc=12,11.71125,46.55464" target="_blank" data-anchor="#filter=r-fullyTranslatedLangus-&amp;zc=12,11.71125,46.55464">Val Gardena Tourist Office</a> website. You can also see the opening status of the routes here.</p>]]></popularWalkingRoutes>
